<br>
Now, looking at some of the Beastlord spells gave me an idea.  They have spells which add a proc to the pets, and you have a choice of cold, fire, poison, magic or disease proc.  So you can choose which will work better against what you are fighting (hmm, sounds like us. . .)<br>
<br>
So, my solution?  Add upper-end SUMMONED weapons for the pets.  The dmg/dly would not be very useful to a PC of course.  But the weapons would have a PROC that would actually be helpful at high end encounters (unlike our vs. summoned swords).<br>
<br>
Level 57, Sword of Frost, procs a Cold based dmg hit, useful for the mobs with high MR and FR that mages can't really do anything against.<br>
Level 58, Sword of Lightning, procs a Lure type spell, more difficult to resist<br>
Level 59, Sword of the giants, procs a low level giantsbane type spell.<br>
Level 60, Sword of the dragon, procs a low level dragonbane type spell.<br>
<br>
The procs would be low level, mabye 50-100pts, but hard to resist vs. certain mobs.  It would add power to the mage class via our PETS, which is really what we should be trying to get.  I don't think we will ever be better nukers and do more damage than some of the other classes without using a pet.<br>
<br>
Perhaps the swords can be level restricted so the procs will only work if pet level is 46+.   Will only work with 57-60 pets and can't hand them out to newbies this way.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p>Zacatac Soulwanderer--High Elf Mage of Bristlebane<br>
