<br>
*) Any new weapon spells along these lines should be very hard to obtain. Getting the spell should be akin to getting a better-than-epic melee weapon. Level 60 quested spells, possibly using research as a step in the quest, would be fun and challenging, with a very nice reward. Or, the weapon could be summoned as an item effect from some reasonably difficult mob.<br>
<br>
*) Keep in mind that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> one</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> magician with summoned pet weapons would benefit all magicians and necromancers on a raid, and possibly charm classes with weapon-wielding mob pets. That has to be taken into effect when discussing balance issues.<br>
<br>
*) There need to be checks against abuse. In particular, there needs to be some reasonable assurance that these new weapons would not be used for farming or soloing. Anything that gave mages an advantage in either of those areas is calling for a quick nerf. Since summoned weapons have the potential to be very long lasting combat buffs, a reasonably high financial investment (reagent) would make them very inefficient to use outside of high-end encounters. That would help ensure that these improvements are used only, or at least mostly, in large raid settings, which is after all the area we would most like to improve. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unandail.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nandail</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 204<br> <font color=#333333>(1/17/02 11:29:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Ok, so here's an idea. . .</span><hr size=1> <br>
Would it be possible to apply some form of Point Analysis to class balance? For those of you geeks out there, I’m thinking something similar to Function Point Analysis.<br>
<br>
Basically what would need to be done would be to come up with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Categories of Balance</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. For example, Group Combat abilities, Solo Combat abilities,  In Combat - Utility abilities, Out of Combat – Utility abilities. Within each of those categories you would have sub categories. For example under Combat, you would have Damage given ability, Damage taken ability, Aggro Reducing ability, Aggro Gaining ability etc...<br>
<br>
At this point you would have to come up with some type of rating system for each ability and then come up with some method of assigning points to the different abilities. Obviously, the tough part would be coming up with a points system that was fair.<br>
<br>
Anyway, what do you think? If it could be done fairly, I would think it would do alot to legitimize class balancing.<br>
